{"_id":"AliciaYoungLove","name":"Alicia - The Young Girl in Love","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":5,"isMainNPC":true,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":3,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I am a young rebel from the slums who knows how to get by on her own","Thanks to my tenacity, I can overcome every obstacle"],"agenda":"I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run away with her to live out our love in peace","background":"Alicia is Alissa's young lover who has infiltrated Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to the two girls' relationship. Alissa had even refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk's heir. Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"infiltrator-rescuer","relationship":"lover-of-alissa"}}
{"_id":"AlissaNorfolk","name":"Alissa of Norfolk","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-woman-tan.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["I have been physically tested by my stay in Wonder","My mind is still strong","My love for Alicia kept me in the real world"],"agenda":"Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a future with Alicia","background":"Alissa is the daughter of the Duke of Norfolk himself. Five months ago, she was taken to Wonder asylum due to her 'too rebellious and unseemly attitude for a young noblewoman.' The truth is that Alissa had refused several promising marriage proposals to remain with her lover Alicia, indifferent to her duty as the Duke's heir. After the first month at Wonder, her letters to her family became more and more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly ceased. According to her words, Wonder is hell on earth where strange presences move in the dark rooms. When she proved incredibly resistant to Alice's 'cures,' the Director imprisoned her in the Hall of the Mind, invading her mind daily with nightmares to quell her rebellious spirit. Despite the physical toll, her love for Alicia has kept her mind strong and anchored to reality."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"rescue-target","relationship":"lover-of-alicia","status":"imprisoned-hall-of-mind"}}
{"_id":"WonderPatient","name":"The Patient of Wonder","type":"npc","img":"icons/environment/people/commoner-weary.webp","system":{"npcType":"villager","oppositionLevel":3,"isMainNPC":false,"attributes":{"soma":{"current":0,"max":0},"wounds":{"current":0,"max":1,"extra":{"value":0,"max":1}}},"descriptors":["We are mad and desperate","Driven to Wonder in the hope of curing our ailments","Madness guides our actions and we no longer understand that there is a world outside the bedlam"],"gifts":[{"name":"Why I Am Here","description":"Roll a die to see what problem led them to Wonder:\n\n1. Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. When they act violently increase their OL by 1.\n\n2. Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and hide with the stolen goods.\n\n3. Abandoned: The Patient was interned at Wonder to be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra Wound.\n\n4. Split personality: The Patient changes personality in the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.\n\n5. Dementia: The Patient is not fully aware of what is happening around them. They are immune to all attempts at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending against a violent action.\n\n6. Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each action against them receives 1 Penalty."}],"background":"Generic patients of the Wonder asylum, driven mad by their conditions and the horrifying 'treatments' administered by Alice Liddell. They roam the Cure Rooms, lost in their own madness, no longer aware of the world outside. They are victims of Alice's twisted experiments in using madness to shape reality."},"flags":{"scenarioId":"wonderbedlam","role":"generic-patient","usage":"use-multiple"}}
